Description: An R translation of the Stata package 'ivppmlhdfe' by Ohyun Kwon,
    Mario Larch, Jangsu Yoon and Yoto V. Yotov, developed in their working paper
    "Instrumental-Variable Poisson PML with High-Dimensional Fixed Effects"
    (CESifo Working Paper 12641, 2026,
    <https://www.ifo.de/en/cesifo/publications/2026/working-paper/instrumental-variable-poisson-pml-high-dimensional-fixed-effects>).
    This package is solely a translation by Guewen Heslan (carried out using
    Claude Opus); all intellectual credit for the estimator, the methodology and
    the original implementation belongs to the original authors. It fits
    instrumental-variable Poisson pseudo-maximum-likelihood (IV-PPML) models
    with multiple sets of high-dimensional fixed effects, solving the additive
    moment condition of Windmeijer and Santos Silva (1997)
    <doi:10.1002/(SICI)1099-1255(199705)12:3%3C281::AID-JAE436%3E3.0.CO;2-1>
    via iteratively reweighted two-stage least squares with the fixed effects
    concentrated out at every iteration following Correia, Guimaraes and Zylkin
    (2020) <doi:10.1177/1536867X20909691>. It provides heteroskedasticity-robust
    and (multi-way) cluster-robust standard errors, automatic detection of
    singletons, fixed-effect separation and ReLU separation, two-stage
    collinearity removal, and the split-panel-jackknife bias correction with
    bootstrap standard errors of the original paper. Plain Poisson PML (no
    instruments) reproduces 'ppmlhdfe' / 'fixest::fepois' point estimates to
    machine precision.
